#!/usr/bin/env bash
# autoutlook: management CLI for Outlook email.
#
# This is a stub. Real implementation is blocked on Microsoft Graph auth
# at the author's tenant (denies user consent to the public Graph CLI
# client and disables user-level app registration). See README.md → Status.
#
# Agents should fall back to driving outlook.office.com via Playwright
# per AGENTS.md until this gets implemented.

set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF' >&2
autoutlook is not implemented yet.

Design + agent contract: see DESIGN.md and AGENTS.md in this repo.
Why no code yet: Microsoft Graph auth is blocked at the author's tenant.

For now, an LLM agent doing email-management work should drive
outlook.office.com directly via Playwright (with persistent storage
state at ~/.config/microsoft-auth/state.json) and follow AGENTS.md
for the protocol — most importantly: sense-check every mutating
action with the human, and propose patches to this CLI for any
case it sees more than once.
EOF
exit 2
